             subtype="h2">12.1. Foretelling good weather.</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_anonymousweather-idp347088">
            <form>
               <orth>[còta]</orth>
            </form>
            <def>“An crochadh tu do chota orra [sic].” In reference to the moon. If you could hang your coat on the moon according to its shape then a good day was in prospect. If you could not then the opposite applied.</def>
